The paper deals with the problem of knowledge inference on large-scale knowledge bases, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed IIKE model involves learning low-dimensional vector representations for entities and relations, which is a common task in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with incomplete and imperfect data, which is a common problem in databases (cs.DB). The model uses a probabilistic approach to measure the probability of each belief, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
